Why apply to Circles.Life?

Circles.Life is not just your digital telco provider. Since our launch, we revolutionised the telco industry by seamlessly integrating both telco and digital lifestyle services on our Circles-X platform. Over the past years, we have captured more than 5% market share in Singapore, launched in Australia and Taiwan while attaining record breaking CSAT and NPS (+50). We were voted the Top Employer in Digital Telco and also became an accredited winner in showcasing excellence in workplace culture in 2019.

As we’re growing to become the biggest and most loved brand, we are looking for: Senior Product Manager - (Telco Growth)

Mission:
The Senior Product Manager (Telco Growth, Singapore) at Circles.Life operates at the exciting intersection of Technology, Design, Strategy and Marketing. You will be responsible for product strategy, competitive intelligence, and contribute to design/pricing in line with our differentiated positioning. Your mission is to continuously understand the digital customer needs and come up with products that fit their needs and align with company plans and resources. You are as much at ease in an industry littered with jargon as you are with exploiting the power of analysis to communicate your views.

As a key member of our team, your responsibilities include:

  Develop and define product strategy, GTM plan, and roadmap for future products to increase customer acquisitions as well as improve retention.
  Deliver high-quality products that exceed customer expectations and take end to end ownership of planning, design, delivery, quality assurance and performance
  Design and run frequent experiments to promote continuous product iterations and improvements
  Partner with marketing, engineering, data science and partnerships to craft growth strategy
  Measure, define and report on growth initiatives and set metric/KPI
  Act as the primary point of contact to successfully release new products on time and within budget
  Drive and provide support to all aspects of the product development plan including but not limited to pricing and positioning
  Understand data savvy customer expectations and industry best practices, including keeping abreast of the technology landscape
  Hunt for insights in data collected from various sources and research to help you come up with continuous actionable improvements
  Keep customer experience first, while developing ways to bolster Customer Acquisition, Usage, and Retention

Requirements:
The talent individual would have/be

  A degree in Business, Marketing or Technology
  At least 8 years in product development and/or product marketing, of which 1- 3 year(s) spent in a B2C business
  Prior experience managing commercial and business metrics within the Telecommunications/ eCommerce domain
  Proven track record in growing customer base and revenue by 100x
  Experience in taking a product from ideation to launch in a B2C environment including revenue generation and customer acquisition of 100X or more
  Strong understanding and hands-on working experience of the technical aspect of product development including but not limited to the agile framework, JIRA, UI/UX and SQL.
  Full end to end experience in driving product adoption, improving conversion funnel for purchase flow to post-live product iteration
  Analytical skills and problem-solving
  Exceptional communication and project management skills

It would be great if the individual had:

  A background in software development/ techinical domain to engage in meaningful conversation with the engineering team.
  Experience in pricing and segmentation
  Research and analysis skills
  Experience working in a fast-paced multicultural environment, especially startups
  Direct working relationship with CXO, board members, investors or founders
